Package ru.introguzzle.parsers.json.entity

Class JSONArray

java.lang.Object
ru.introguzzle.parsers.common.util.DelegatingArray<Object>
ru.introguzzle.parsers.common.util.UntypedArray
ru.introguzzle.parsers.json.entity.JSONArray
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Iterable<Object>, Collection<Object>, Consumer<Visitor<JSONArray>>, List<Object>, SequencedCollection<Object>, Visitable<JSONArray,Visitor<JSONArray>>, JSONStringConvertable
public class JSONArray extends UntypedArray implements JSONStringConvertable, Visitable<JSONArray,Visitor<JSONArray>>, Serializable
Represents a JSON array as a list of objects.

This class extends UntypedArray and provides functionality for storing and manipulating JSON array data. It implements the JSONStringConvertable interface for conversion to JSON string representation and supports the visitor pattern via the Visitable interface.

Features:

  • Store and retrieve elements of various permitted types.
  • Type-specific getters for common JSON data types.
  • Customizable addition of elements with type checking.
  • Conversion to JSONObject using key extraction and remapping functions.

Usage Example:


 JSONArray jsonArray = new JSONArray();
 jsonArray.add("String value");
 jsonArray.add(42);
 jsonArray.add(true);

 // Access elements
 String stringValue = jsonArray.getString(0); // "String value"
 Number numberValue = jsonArray.getNumber(1); // 42
 Boolean booleanValue = jsonArray.getBoolean(2); // true
 );
Note: all methods that are related to storing elements may throw IllegalArgumentException if class of element to be stored is not permitted according to PERMITTED_CLASSES. This behaviour depends on boolean entityValidationEnabled flag in configuration
